## `app/(tabs)/(home)/index.ios.tsx` (iOS — 354 lines)
Simplified iOS version of `(home)/index.tsx`. Client view: logo, greeting, "Post a New Gig" button → `router.push('/post-gig')`, posted gigs list (renders `gig.title` only — **note: no `gig.category`/`gig.description`/status badge**). Provider view: subscribe card or gigs list (also renders `gig.title` only). No direct offer handling, no modal.

---

## `app/(tabs)/profile.tsx` (Android/Web — 932 lines)
Client profile shows: logo, avatar initials (red circle), name, email. Then for clients: recent gig card (fetched from `/api/gigs/client/${user.id}`), matched providers list with Select buttons, countdown timer (180s), waiting state. For providers: subscription status card. Both: Account Information section (type, county, org, gender, phone). Red "Log Out" button → `logout()` + `router.replace('/role-select')`. Polls every 5s when gig is open. Uses `useFocusEffect` to refetch on tab focus.

